pageContext.description: Of torque type, made by twisting a four-leaved bar. The twisted portion ends, on each side, in a collar, from which spring the terminals for passing through the ears.
pageContext.associations: It forms a pair with No. 415, Plate XVIII, & was found in the same place.
pageContext.collection: National Museum of Science & Art, Dublin, Plate XVIII, 416, W 64., formerly in collection of Major H.C. Sirr.
pageContext.site: Ireland, Co Roscommon, near Castlereagh (said to have been found)
pageContext.museumCollection: National Museum of Science & Art, Dublin
